news.title: Poor response to Chandigarh housing board auctions
news.para: Nearly a year ago, CHB had offered on auction its 92 commercial properties. Of these, it again offered 88 commercial properties last month, but failed to find any takers.

news.title: Bengaluru: 15 lakh properties without khata under scanner
news.para: BBMP chief commissioner Tushar Giri Nath said the city has more than 20 lakh ‘A’ khata and 7 lakh ‘B’ khata properties. Many owners allegedly do not opt for ‘B’ khata’ to avoid property tax payment.

news.title: Odisha CM inaugurates three housing complexes for slum dwellers in Bhubaneswar
news.para: The three housing complexes inaugurated by Patnaik were: Keshari Residency built in Satya Nagar, Buddha Vihar in Chandrasekharpur and Barunei Enclave in Subudhipur.

news.title: Gurugram: 16 building sites fined Rs 7 lakh for GRAP violations, owners served notices
news.para: On behalf of the deputy commissioner, district town planner (planning) and three district town planners (enforcement) have been appointed as duty magistrates to tackle violations of GRAP rules.

news.title: Bengaluru: 26 buildings in layout face BBMP action over building plan violations
news.para: As part of its crackdown, BBMP identified 70 buildings in the layout and demanded that the owners submit their approved plans. Of the 30 plans received, 26 were found to be in violation, encompassing unauthorised additional floors and failure to adhere to setbacks.

news.title: Wipro to sell office assets in Hyderabad, Bengaluru
news.para: The country's fourth-largest IT firm recently implemented a compulsory hybrid work policy requiring employees to report to work from the office at least three days a week.

news.title: Gurugram: 96 cases filed, 29 held for illegal construction in four months
news.para: Police said on Monday that the cases were registered after the Enforcement Bureau police station was set up in Gurgaon.

news.title: MahaRERA suspends registration of 248 projects over failure to update reports
news.para: ​Similarly, the registration of 224 projects registered in March are likely to be suspended for not updating their quarterly project reports.

news.title: Mumbai: BMC cuts tin sheet height rule for building sites to 25 feet over structural stability
news.para: The BMC guidelines issued on October 25 had stated that all project proponents must ensure at least 35-foot-high tin metal sheets are erected around construction projects that are more than 70 metres in height.

news.title: Mumbai: FIR on Bharat Developer for not adhering to pollution rules
news.para: A civic officer said six squads were formed for the K-West ward. The squad for the Santacruz police station region had issued a copy of air pollution mitigation guidelines on November 8 to the site addressed at Bharat Developer in Vile Parle (West) earlier this month.

news.title: Delhi-RERA's order stalls registration of properties
news.para: ​RERA also asked the civic bodies not to clear building plans that had more than the permissible number of dwelling units mandated by UBBL according to the plot size.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh set to unveil plan to revive stalled projects
news.para: Keenly watched by realtors and homebuyers, the package is likely to contain a rescheduling scheme that allows dues, builders owe to the state, to be settled in instalments.

news.title: Everest Food Products promoters buy flat in Mumbai's Worli for Rs 73.50 crore
news.para: The apartment spread over 6,130 sq ft carpet area is located on the 37th habitable floor of the Oberoi Three Sixty West tower. The deal is valued at over Rs 1.16 lakh per sq ft.

news.title: Global slowdown blues to stall demand growth for office space this fiscal: Crisil
news.para: According to Crisil Ratings the inherent strengths of the Indian market and increasing shift to return to office, however, should help demand pick up over the medium term, keeping credit profiles of office asset owners stable.

news.title: Global Capability Centres to lease 60-62 million sq ft space in 2023-25 across top six cities: Report
news.para: Global Capability Centres are now leasing larger offices with the potential to scale up in the future. Availability and cost of talent, real estate, and supporting regulatory framework aid GCCs expansion in India.

news.title: Haryana government to refund development fees of Rs 5.19 crore to 1,588 property owners
news.para: The government made this decision upon becoming aware of the situation. As a result, a total of 1588 property owners will receive a refund.

news.title: New colonies spring up in Jaipur, wait for roads continues
news.para: Villagers in the area said the sitting BJP legislator, Satish Poonia, who is seeking re-election in Amber, has visited them several times in the last couple years.

news.title: Tamil Nadu CM inaugurates 4,272 flats built at cost of Rs 453.67 crore
news.para: ​The chief minister also inaugurated a newly constructed multistoried apartment housing of 32 units, constructed at a cost of Rs 31.26 crore, in Tirunelveli district on Monday.

news.title: PWD to take a second shot at installing over 1,000 streetlights in Delhi
news.para: According to officials, these streetlights are being installed as part of the Chief Minister's streetlight project. Bids were called earlier also but they could not attract many bidders.

news.title: Gujarat: 80 Narmada resettlement colonies to be part of villages
news.para: Eighty resettlement colonies will be included in villages of Bharuch, Narmada, Chhota Udepur, Vadodara, Kheda and Panchmahal districts, an official statement said.
